cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning methods, specifically recurrent neural networks, to remote sensing data for land cover classification. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of deep learning for feature representation and classification also relates to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. Finally, the use of satellite imagery and spatial data may also relate to graphics (cs.GR) subcategory.
